<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 4:23PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southeastern Madison
County through 500 PM MDT...
At 422 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 13 miles southwest of Virginia City to 26 miles
northeast of Monida. Movement was east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Ennis, Cameron and Jeffers.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
